# Playwright E2E Testing Rule

## Core Expectations

- Write deterministic tests: avoid arbitrary waits like `waitForTimeout`.
- Use user-visible locators (`getByRole`, `getByLabel`, `getByText`) before CSS selectors.
- Keep tests isolated: no shared mutable state between tests.
- Use clear Arrange-Act-Assert flow in each test body.
- Once you are done making changes to the codebase, run all the tests and ensure they pass.
- Once you are done making changes, proactively ask the user if you should also write new tests to cover a new functionality.

## Reliability Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
await page.waitForTimeout(1500);
await page.click('.submit-btn');

// ✅ GOOD
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' }).click();
await expect(page.getByText('Saved')).toBeVisible();
```

## Assertion Guidance

- Assert behavior the user can observe, not implementation details.
- Prefer `toBeVisible`, `toHaveURL`, and `toHaveText` over weak truthy checks.
- Keep one primary intent per test; split broad scenarios into multiple tests.
